 * ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
 * ║  [Admin System] DINOCO SN Approval Workflow                      ║
 * ║  Version: V.0.1 (2026-05-05) — Phase 2 W5 4-eyes approval queue ║
 * ║  DB_ID: (pending — populate after first WP Code Snippets sync)  ║
 * ║  Description: Approval request lifecycle for S/N system.        ║
 * ║    Atomic state machine (pending/approved/rejected/expired/     ║
 * ║    cancelled) with self-approval block + SLA cron + LINE/Tele   ║
 * ║    notifications. Action callback fires `dinoco_sn_approval_*`  ║
 * ║    do_action hooks so executor snippets handle state transition.║
 * ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
 *
 * Plan: ~/.claude/plans/wiki-doc-sequential-lantern.md v2.13 §2.7
 * Architecture: docs/sn-system/01-system-architecture.md
 * State machine: docs/sn-system/02-state-machine.md
 *
 * Dependencies (all `function_exists` guarded — defensive):
 *   - [System] DINOCO SN REST API V.0.18+        — classifier + idempotency wrapper
 *   - [Admin System] DINOCO Production SN Manager — table helpers + audit log
 *   - [Admin System] DINOCO User Role Manager     — capability registration
 *   - [Admin System] DINOCO Idempotency Helper    — POST replay protection
 *
 * REST endpoints registered (Phase 2 W5):
 *   POST   /dinoco-sn/v1/approval/request                — actor creates request
 *   POST   /dinoco-sn/v1/approval/(?P<uuid>[a-f0-9-]+)/approve  — approver decides
 *   POST   /dinoco-sn/v1/approval/(?P<uuid>[a-f0-9-]+)/reject   — approver rejects
 *   POST   /dinoco-sn/v1/approval/(?P<uuid>[a-f0-9-]+)/cancel   — actor cancels own
 *   GET    /dinoco-sn/v1/approval/pending                — admin viewer (paginated)
 *   GET    /dinoco-sn/v1/approval/(?P<uuid>[a-f0-9-]+)   — request detail
 *
 * SLA cron:
 *   dinoco_sn_approval_sla_cron — every 15 min — auto-expire past expires_at
 *   Heartbeat: dinoco_cron_sn_approval_sla_last_run option (Round 28+ pattern)
 *
 * Action hooks fired after approve():
 *   do_action( 'dinoco_sn_approval_approved', $uuid, $action, $context, $approver_id )
 *   do_action( 'dinoco_sn_approval_rejected', $uuid, $action, $context, $approver_id, $notes )
 *   do_action( 'dinoco_sn_approval_expired',  $uuid, $action, $context )
 *   do_action( 'dinoco_sn_approval_cancelled', $uuid, $action, $context, $actor_id )
 *
 * Listeners can wire `dinoco_sn_approval_approved` to actually execute the
 * state transition (swap/void/recall/reissue/relink). This snippet does NOT
 * mutate sn_pool itself — it only orchestrates approval.
 *
 * DESIGN PRINCIPLES
 *   - ADDITIVE   — table installs lazily on admin_init, no other side effects
 *   - DEFENSIVE  — all cross-snippet calls function_exists guarded, no-op if missing
 *   - ATOMIC     — GET_LOCK + START TRANSACTION + try/catch ROLLBACK pattern
 *   - IDEMPOTENT — every POST uses dinoco_sn_with_idempotency() wrapper
 *   - AUDIT      — every state transition logs via dinoco_sn_audit_log()
 *   - SELF-BLOCK — actor === approver returns 422 + audit trail
 */

